-- China May Boost Rates by Half Point `Within Weeks,' Credit Suisse Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-11T03:31:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/china-may-boost-rates-by-half-point-within-weeks-credit-suisse-says.html
The Chinese government may raise
interest rates by half a percentage point “within weeks,”
according to Credit Suisse Group AG.  The brokerage forecast the inflation rate will exceed 6
percent by the middle of 2011 as predictions growth in consumer
prices would peak in the third quarter have “failed to
materialize,” according to a report to clients.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
